const pageContent = "<div class=\"mc-about\">\n\n  <h1>Custom Illustration Services for Brands, Bands &#x26; Campaigns — Australia</h1>\n\nMitch Chadban is an Australian illustrator and designer creating custom commercial illustration for brand campaigns, music releases, merch, packaging, and corporate communications. Based in Australia and working with clients nationally, Mitch produces illustration that is recognisable, ownable, and built for the real world — print, digital, and everything in between.\n\n  <br /><br />\nIf your brand (or band) needs visuals with personality — not stock imagery, not AI slop — this is the place.\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <a href=\"/contact-form/\" ><div class=\"custom-btn\"><b>Enquire about Illustration</b></div></a>\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <div class=\"img-full-ctm\">\n    <img class=\"zoomable\" src=\"https://freight.cargo.site/w/1600/i/E2839865389350325557825318803929/Illustration-for-Bands--Brands----Everything-In-Between-bands.png\" alt=\"Cheesy stock photo in a rehearsal studio: a band (guitar, drums) stands around a corporate-looking person in a blazer who is giving a thumbs up at a giant illustrated poster board. The poster shows colourful abstract art with no readable text. Everyone is overly enthusiastic, staged, bright lighting, slightly uncanny AI vibe, wide banner, no logos.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1080\" height=\"720\">\n  </div>\n\n  <br />\n\n  <h2>What Custom Illustration Is Used For</h2>\n\nCustom illustration gives brands and artists a signature visual identity that is theirs alone. Unlike stock imagery or AI-generated visuals, commissioned illustration is built around your specific brief, audience, and use-case. Common applications include campaign hero imagery, merch and apparel graphics, product packaging, gig posters, album artwork, website and landing page visuals, social content, and internal communications.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\nThe right illustration does three things: it creates recognition, communicates personality, and holds attention longer than a photo ever could.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <h2>Illustration Services</h2>\n\n  <h3>Band &#x26; Music Illustration</h3>\nIllustration for releases, tours, and merch that people actually want to own. This includes gig posters and tour artwork, album and single cover illustration, merch graphics for tees, hoodies, and stickers, and social content and promo assets. Music illustration works best when the visual has its own personality — something that extends the sound into a look.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <h3>Brand &#x26; Campaign Illustration</h3>\nWhen a campaign needs a distinctive visual language that doesn&#x27;t look like every other brand in the category. Services include campaign hero illustrations, website and landing page illustration, social content series, ad creative and digital banners. Brand illustration is particularly effective for businesses that want to own a visual style across multiple touchpoints rather than swapping stock images every season.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <h3>Corporate Illustration</h3>\nCorporate illustration doesn&#x27;t have to be boring. Clear, considered illustration makes internal communications more human, simplifies complex information, and gives presentations and events a more considered look. This covers internal comms visuals, training and explainer graphics, icon sets and spot illustrations, and event collateral and presentation graphics.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <h3>Packaging &#x26; Product Illustration</h3>\nPackaging illustration for brands that need shelf presence or scroll-stopping energy. This includes full label artwork, packaging illustration, product story visuals, and limited edition collab artwork. Good packaging illustration earns its keep — it works at thumbnail size, at shelf scale, and everywhere in between.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <h2>Custom Portraits &#x26; Pet Portraits</h2>\n\nFor personal commissions — gifts, keepsakes, or because your dog deserves art on the wall — Mitch also offers custom portrait and pet portrait commissions.\n\n  <ul>\n    <li><a href=\"/portrait-commissions-(digital-+-print)/\" >Custom Portraits — more info here</a></li>\n    <li><a href=\"/custom-pet-portraits-(digital-+-print)/\" >Pet Portraits — more info here</a></li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <br />\n\n  <h2>How the Illustration Process Works</h2>The process is straightforward and built around not wasting your time.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <strong>Step 1 — Brief</strong><br />\nYou share what you need: what it&#x27;s for, where it will be used (print, digital, or both), any style references, your deadline, and format requirements. The more specific the better — vague briefs produce vague work.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <strong>Step 2 — Direction &#x26; Sketch</strong><br />\nA rough concept direction is shared before any detailed work starts. This is where we align on composition, tone, and approach — so there are no surprises at the end.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <strong>Step 3 — Final Artwork</strong><br />\nThe illustration is refined and delivered in production-ready formats. You get files that actually work in the real world — not just something that looks good on screen.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <strong>Step 4 — Handover</strong><br />\nFinal delivery includes web and print formats, and source/editable files if needed. Clear, clean, no drama.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <div class=\"img-full-ctm\">\n    <img class=\"zoomable\" src=\"https://freight.cargo.site/w/1600/i/M2839865389368772301899028355545/Illustration-for-Bands--Brands----Everything-In-Between-Present.png\" alt=\"Overly staged corporate meeting where executives in suits point at a wall of whimsical cartoon doodles and icons like it\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1080\" height=\"720\">\n  </div>\n\n  <br />\n\n  <h2>Illustration Packages</h2>\n\n  <strong>Option A — Single Illustration</strong><br />\nOne piece, built for a specific use-case: a gig poster, hero image, merch graphic, or campaign visual. Best for one-off projects with a clear brief and defined output.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <strong>Option B — Illustration Set</strong><br />\nMultiple pieces in a consistent style — best for campaigns, merch drops, or content series where visual cohesion across formats matters. Includes format variations.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <strong>Option C — Ongoing Illustration Support</strong><br />\nFor brands that need regular illustration and want a consistent style across everything they produce — without briefing a new illustrator every time.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\nTell me what you&#x27;re building and where it will live. I&#x27;ll recommend the right approach and be upfront about what&#x27;s possible within your timeline.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <h2>Why Commission Custom Illustration Instead of Using Stock or AI?</h2>\n\nStock imagery is recognisable as stock. AI-generated images are increasingly recognisable as AI. Custom illustration is the only visual option that is genuinely yours — built to your brief, aligned to your brand, and impossible to reverse-image-search back to a library.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\nFor brands in competitive categories — food and beverage, music, lifestyle, corporate comms — custom illustration is one of the most durable visual investments available. It scales from a sticker to a billboard without losing quality. It works on merch. It works in digital. It compounds over time as the style becomes recognisable.\n\n  <br /><br />\n\n  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions — Custom Illustration Services</h2>\n\n  <h3>What does a custom illustration service in Australia typically include?</h3>\nA custom illustration service covers the full process from brief through to production-ready artwork. This includes concept direction, rough sketches for alignment, refined final artwork, and delivery in the correct formats for your intended use — web, print, or both. Mitch Chadban offers illustration services across all of these stages for clients across Australia.\n\n\n <h3>How much does custom illustration cost in Australia?</h3>\nCustom illustration pricing in Australia varies based on complexity, usage rights, and the number of pieces required. A single illustration for a gig poster or campaign hero typically starts from a few hundred dollars. Sets and ongoing retainers are priced based on scope. The best approach is to send a brief and get a real number rather than guessing from a rate card.\n\n  <h3>What illustration styles are available?</h3>\nStyle adapts to the project — from clean and minimal to bold character-driven illustration. The approach is guided by your brand, your audience, and where the work will live. If you have references, bring them. If not, a clear brief is usually enough to establish the right direction.\n\n  <h3>Can illustration be used for both print and digital?</h3>\nYes. All illustration is delivered in formats appropriate for each output — high-resolution files for print and optimised files for digital. Screen printing-ready artwork, embroidery-ready files, and assets built for DTG merch are available on request.\n\n\n  <h3>How long does custom illustration take?</h3>\n  Turnaround depends on the complexity of the brief and the number of pieces required. Most projects move quickly once direction is confirmed. If you have a hard deadline, share it upfront — a realistic timeline is always better than a rushed result.\n\n\n  <h3>Do you illustrate for music artists and bands as well as brands?</h3>Yes. Mitch Chadban works across both commercial brand illustration and music illustration — gig posters, album artwork, merch graphics, and tour assets. The brief and process are the same regardless of whether the client is a band or a business.\n\n  <h3>Can you match an existing brand style or illustration system?</h3>\nYes. If you have existing brand guidelines or an established illustration style, work can be extended to match it. If you&#x27;re building from scratch, a new illustration style can be developed that complements your existing brand identity.\n\n\n  <h3>Ready for custom illustration that&#x27;s actually yours?</h3>\nSend a brief — what it&#x27;s for, where it will be used, and your deadline. Even rough ideas are fine to start with.\n\n  <a href=\"/contact-form/\" ><div class=\"custom-btn\"><b>Enquire about Illustration</b></div></a>\n<br />\n  <br />\n</div>\n\n<!--  <script>\n{\n  \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n  \"@type\": \"LocalBusiness\",\n  \"name\": \"Mitch Chadban\",\n  \"url\": \"https://mitchchadban.com\",\n  \"description\": \"Custom illustration services for brands, bands, campaigns, packaging, and corporate communications. Based in Australia, working with clients nationally.\",\n  \"address\": {\n    \"@type\": \"PostalAddress\",\n    \"addressCountry\": \"AU\"\n  },\n  \"areaServed\": {\n    \"@type\": \"Country\",\n    \"name\": \"Australia\"\n  },\n  \"priceRange\": \"$$\",\n  \"hasOfferCatalog\": {\n    \"@type\": \"OfferCatalog\",\n    \"name\": \"Illustration Services\",\n    \"itemListElement\": [\n      {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"itemOffered\": {\n          \"@type\": \"Service\",\n          \"name\": \"Band & Music Illustration\",\n          \"description\": \"Custom illustration for music releases, gig posters, album artwork, tour assets, and merch graphics.\"\n        }\n      },\n      {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"itemOffered\": {\n          \"@type\": \"Service\",\n          \"name\": \"Brand & Campaign Illustration\",\n          \"description\": \"Custom illustration for brand campaigns, website and landing pages, social content series, and digital ad creative.\"\n        }\n      },\n      {\n        \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n        \"itemOffered\": {\n          \"@type\": \"Service\",\n          \"name\": \"Corporate Illustration\",\n          \"description\": \"Illustration for internal communications, training materials, explainer graphics, icon sets, and presentati